<!channel> - FYI next week  (Thurs Nov 10) PEPPER the ROBOT  will be taking over Galvanize from 9am-9pm and you are invited to interact whenever you can between class :smiley:
More details here:

RSVP <https://www.eventbrite.com/e/pepper-day-program-your-first-robot-at-galvanize-san-francisco-tickets-28760689998>

DESCRIPTION
November 10th is Pepper Day at Galvanize San Francisco!
SoftBank Robotics is bringing Pepper to Galvanize to showcase “Robotics as a Platform” and the natural evolution of the user interface.

You Will Learn:
1.   How robots can bridge the gap between humans and technology – you will learn about exciting use cases for Pepper
2.   How the Internet of Things will become integral to Pepper and the future of robotics.
3.   How developers working on Pepper today are setting the standards for the future of robotics.
4.   How you can get involved in the next wave of innovation

Pepper Day Agenda:

9am-12pm – “Coffee With Pepper”
Have a coffee on Pepper in the Galvanize Cafe! The Softbank Robotics team will be available to demonstrate some of her basic functionality.
12-2pm – “Lunch & Learn With Pepper”
Have lunch on Pepper, and learn more about the opportunities to build on Pepper’s open platform. This is a forum to allow people to dive a little deeper.
6-9pm – “Programming Your First Robot”
Join us for an evening event that brings the tech community (i.e. developers, data scientists, founder, etc.) together for an opportunity to see Pepper in action, hear from her creators, and learn more about ways to engage with and build on Pepper.

More About Pepper:

Pepper runs on an OS called NAOqi It is an embedded GNU/Linux distribution based on Gentoo, and has been tailored specifically to fit Pepper and NAO’s needs. SDK’s allow you to create modules to run on NAOqi with Matlab, Python, C++, .net and MS Robotics Studio.

"G’day all, yes this was written by an Aussie, and it is because the Australian resource industry is coming to SF this weekend for Unearthed (<http://unearthed.solutions/>).

Unearthed is a 54 hour hackathon that features huge industry challenges and datasets from some of the world’s largest resource companies. This weekend at Galvanize we are hosting 2 challenges from Caterpillar and BHP Billiton, both from deep within their operations and we are offering up unique opportunities for data scientists and developers. Not only are there great prizes (thousands of dollars) but both organisations are looking for top tech talent here in SF so as to continue developing projects and working with individuals out of the hackathon. The top team will also have their project filmed and presented in front of hundreds of thousands next week in Las Vegas at MINExpo.

Developers and data scientists of all skills and backgrounds are invited to attend. If you have no experience in this industry it often serves as a benefit as you come in with fresh ideas and a new input that these organisations have never seen before. By participating you will get in front of these global organisations and open yourself up to a world of opportunities within the industry. You will also join a global community of over 1500 entrepreneurs and innovators from Unearthed events.
